## Verification Plan
### Automated Tests
- Unit tests for backend endpoints using Jest.
- Front‑end component tests with Jest + jsdom (e.g., journal entry rendering, mood log UI).
- Integration test: simulate user flow (journal → mood log → analysis → motivational prompt) and assert points increment.

### Manual Verification
- Load the app in Chrome/Edge, test on both desktop and mobile viewports.
- Verify dark‑mode appearance and glassmorphism effects.
- Conduct a short user‑testing session with a student to assess emotional trigger detection relevance.

### Acceptance Criteria
- All core features (journal, mood log, motivation bot, mindfulness) functional.
- Gamification points & badges display correctly.
- AI trigger report updates after each new entry.
- No sensitive data stored without user consent; privacy notice displayed on first launch.

